The below code is to sort the array in bubble sort
And the difference between the selection and bubble sort are
selection sort will sort the lowest elements and
the bubble sort will sort first the highest element in the end.



public class bubble {
    public static void main (String args[]){
        int arr[] = new int[]{50,2,45,1,4,-1,-45,12,65};
        bubble_sort(arr);
        

    }
    public static void bubble_sort(int a[]){
        for(int i =0; i<a.length - 1; i++){
            for(int j =0; j<a.length - 1 - i; j++){
                if(a[j] > a[j+1]){
                    int temp = a[j];
                    a[j] = a[j+1];
                    a[j+1] = temp;

                }
            }
        }
        for(int l : a){
            System.out.println(l);
        }
    }
    
}
